<div type="definition">
<p>FRIED so as to BECOME BRITTLE AND SAVOURY.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. A common general term for crisp is wēi 脆.</p>
<p>2. Sū 酥 refers to something crisp and easy to smash, but the word is not current in pre-Buddhist literature.</p>
        </div>
